Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
In-fill site surrounded by abundance of hotels,
restaurants and service retailers. Located in the
highly desirable Lake Mary / Heathrow submarket
with close proximity to Interstate 4 (I-4), State
Road-417(Toll) and 10 miles East of Sanford/Orlando
Intl. Airport.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The Tampa North Aero Park includes 21 acres of land, three platted residential lots, office and hangar buildings, a fuel farm, runway annual easement income fees, a licensed Lasergrade and PSI testing facility and a licensed FAA Repair Station. The airport is an attractive investment opportunity for a variety of aviation venues, including those who desire to start or expand an FBO, flight school, or aircraft maintenance business.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Full-sized basketball courts, Volleyball courts, & Gazebos
4 commercial kitchens with attached dining/meeting rooms
1 large meeting room, 1 large food service kitchen

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: 4.5 Acres of private grounds, sleeps 598. Steps from public beach access and 300' of frontage on Front Beach Road.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Oceanside camp surrounded by resorts, family entertainment, shopping, and outdoor recreation! The campus is on the sugar white sands of the Gulf of Mexico on the west end of the beach.
